  <h2>Recommended protocol</h2>

  <pre><code>/q-frame  → /q-char  → /q-explore → /q-compare → /q-decide
  what's      what       genuinely     fair         engineering
  broken?     matters?   different     comparison   contract
                         options</code></pre>

  <p>
    You can enter at any step, but the protocol works best in order. <code>/q-char</code> before
    <code>/q-explore</code> prevents bias (criteria defined before options). <code>/q-compare</code>
    before <code>/q-decide</code> ensures fair evaluation.
  </p>

